                              <dir-section id="LT.DIR.598" sllink="SLSDOC" slsdocrf="DIR-SECTREF" usage="ewyb casee">
                                   <heading>
                                        <b>Lithuanian Orthodox Church (Moscow Patriarchate)</b>
                                   </heading>
                                   <p id="LT.DIR.217">The first Orthodox communities in Lithuania appeared during the 12th century. While Lithuania formed part of the Russian Empire (1795-1915), Orthodoxy was considered the state religion. The Lithuanian Orthodox Church emphasizes that despite its official links with the Moscow Patriarchate, in practice, it operates independently of Russian influence.</p>
