                    <dir-section id="LT.DIR.230" sllink="SLSDOC" slsdocrf="DIR-SECTREF" usage="ewyb casee">
                         <heading>Islam</heading>
                         <p id="LT.DIR.231">Sunni Islam is the religion of the ethnic Tatars of Lithuania. The first Tatar communities settled there in the 14th century. The first mosque in Vilnius was erected in 1558.</p>
                    </dir-section>
                    <dir-section id="LT.DIR.233" sllink="SLSDOC" slsdocrf="DIR-SECTREF" usage="ewyb casee">
                         <heading>Judaism</heading>
                         <p id="LT.DIR.234">The first Jewish communities appeared in Lithuania in the 15th century. In the 15th-17th centuries Vilnius was an important centre of Jewish culture and religion. Before the Second World War approximately 200,000 Jews lived in Lithuania; an estimated 90% were murdered during the German occupation (1941-44). There is a small number of Karaites (Karaim), who originate from Crimea, who speak a Turkic language and follow a form of Judaism, resident in Lithuania.</p>
